This module is right around the handle of my wizard staff, and it has a few functions.

1. OLED Display
  a. This is run using 2 screens, .96" OLED displays
  b. I kept them with the same address, so they display the same thing
  c. They have a bar of yellow at the top that I use as an info pane, displaying compass bearing, temperature, and humidity.
  d. The rest is used as a sort of graphical representation. There is a bar that represents 0, and the points of a floating triangle are temp, humidity, and a fixed one. 
    There is also a filled circle with some spotty code representing compass bearing.
2. Temperature
    from a temp/humidity module
3. Humidity
    from the very same aforementioned temp/humidity module
4. Compass
    from a 3-axis magnetometer, which I'm sure could have more functions, but preliminary search didn't yield much. Maybe a cell phone detector? I don't know.
5. Multicolor LED
    another way to represent actions and inputs to the module. The buttons change the color based on what they're doing, then it returns to normal after 4 seconds
6. Button 1
    Game button
    I made a simple 6-sided dice left/right/everybody drinking game button that changes the LED color and displays the result text on the screens
7. Button 2
    Alignment button
    It checks the compass bearing (69 degrees is the target currently) and then shows an animation and displays success/unaligned, and changes the color of the LED

It has a handful of libraries it uses (all listed in the includes, nothing weird), and I put it all together on the Arduino IDE, since it's one file.
This is on a Uno R3, I will add pinouts in next update.
